                            <comment id="12948697" author="janstey" created="Fri, 5 Sep 2008 14:26:18 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;See comment from Willem in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CAMEL-460&quot; title=&quot;Add spring unit tests for the intercept() feature&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CAMEL-460&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CAMEL-460&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&quot; InterceptType also not support take the predicate from XML,&lt;br/&gt;
if I put a ChoiceType member in the interceptType , I will create a Cycle dependency between the InterceptType and ChoiceType.&quot;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12950892" author="davsclaus" created="Wed, 18 Feb 2009 13:30:55 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Okay its the &amp;lt;stop/&amp;gt; that is the problem, the predicate is supported and it works fine.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;However its only the &amp;lt;stop/&amp;gt; that is the problem as it gets global and stops always&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-xml&quot;&gt;        &lt;span class=&quot;code-tag&quot;&gt;&amp;lt;intercept&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;
            &lt;span class=&quot;code-tag&quot;&gt;&amp;lt;when&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;
                &lt;span class=&quot;code-tag&quot;&gt;&amp;lt;simple&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;${body} contains &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&apos;Goofy&apos;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;code-tag&quot;&gt;&amp;lt;/simple&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;
                &lt;span class=&quot;code-tag&quot;&gt;&amp;lt;to uri=&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;mock:goofy&quot;&lt;/span&gt;/&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;
            &lt;span class=&quot;code-tag&quot;&gt;&amp;lt;/when&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;
            &lt;span class=&quot;code-tag&quot;&gt;&amp;lt;stop/&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;
        &lt;span class=&quot;code-tag&quot;&gt;&amp;lt;/intercept&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We only want it to stop if the predicate is true. Its silly to stop always as it will intercept all and just stop. So we might wanna do some tricks on the Spring DSL side and only perform stop if the predicate was evaluated to true.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12950875" author="davsclaus" created="Thu, 19 Feb 2009 11:55:03 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Fixed in trunk&lt;br/&gt;
Committed revision 745826.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
